-- Kazakh bank Halyk sees 2014 net profit rising to $494 mln
-- By Dmitry Solovyov
-- Mon May 19, 2014 09:08AM EDT
-- None



ALMATY, May 19 (Reuters) - Kazakhstan's Halyk Bank <HSBK.KZ> <HSBKq.L>, the Central Asian nation's second-largest lender by assets, said on Monday it expects its net profit to rise by nearly a quarter to 90 billion tenge ($494 million) this year from 72.2 billion in 2013.

Halyk forecasts its net interest margin - an indicator of a bank's efficiency - to rise to 5.0 percent in 2014 from 4.9 percent in 2013, it said in a presentation for investors.